    <a title="Andy Marr" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/8228243-andy-marr"><img alt="Andy Marr" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1602706259p2/8228243.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2937012665?book_show_action=true">Mar 29, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Andy Marr" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Andy Marr" href="/user/show/8228243-andy-marr">Andy Marr</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/6530484-the-secret-scripture">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2937012665" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16096134955779268582">I really wish Goodreads offered the chance to award half-stars. This was my second Sebastian Barry novel, after Days Without End, which I read back in 2018. While TSS wasn&apos;t quite poor enough to gain three stars, DWE wasn&apos;t good enough to gain five, and so, despite enjoying one far less than the other, both get four stars. It hardly seems fair, really.<br/><br/>Incidentally, this would have earned the full four stars if I hadn&apos;t guessed the &apos;surprise twist&apos; at precisely the 31% mark (this despite the fact</span>
  <span id="freeText16096134955779268582" style="display:none">I really wish Goodreads offered the chance to award half-stars. This was my second Sebastian Barry novel, after Days Without End, which I read back in 2018. While TSS wasn't quite poor enough to gain three stars, DWE wasn't good enough to gain five, and so, despite enjoying one far less than the other, both get four stars. It hardly seems fair, really.<br /><br />Incidentally, this would have earned the full four stars if I hadn't guessed the 'surprise twist' at precisely the 31% mark (this despite the fact I'm notoriously stupid when it comes to plot twists). The prose was also slightly overdone in places, though all in all I'm rather in love with Barry's writing.</span>
  <a data-text-id="16096134955779268582" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
